10: That should take care of them.
15:
Damn, girl! Is this what the navy's 
making nowadays?
19:
Foes of this caliber should be no 
problem. Just leave it to me.
29: Look... I'm sorry we lost the ship.
31:
It looks like it'll be a bit longer before 
you can reach the northern waters.
34: No... I should apologize as well.
37:
A ship I was on has sunk. I really must 
be the reaper...
41:
Ahahaha! Don't give yourself TOO 
much credit for that one.
44:
I mean, sure, the ship sank. But on the 
bright side, we all survived! And there's 
loads of booty to find here!
46:
Lady Luck's had my back more times 
than I can count, so don't concern 
yourself over every hiccup along the 
way!
51: If you say so, that's what I will do.
54:
This wasn't a complete loss for me 
either. I've already made a few 
significant discoveries.
56:
This architecture, for example. I'm sure 
it was part of a major city long ago 
before it sank.
63:
A skyscraper made of mythril—
I remember seeing a building with this 
exact description in official Gaean 
documents.
64:
There was once a government agency 
known as the Ministry of Oracles. This 
building was likely their headquarters.
67:
Oracles? You mean people who 
supposedly interpret divine 
messages? I wouldn't expect THEM of 
all people to have such a futuristic-
looking building.
70:
I also thought it was strange at first. 
However, if a door existed here that 
could travel between worlds...
73:
I guess it wouldn't seem that strange 
at all, huh?
76:
We could even consider the possibility 
that the rising sea levels weren't 
caused by something in our world, but 
another one entirely.
78:
In any case, whatever caused it... I'll 
make sure they get their 
comeuppance.
81: Ha! Now you're talking my language!
84:
There's only one way to find out for 
sure, right?
88:
The culprit who did this to our world 
may very well still be out there—what 
do you say?
92:
I appreciate the offer, but I'll have to 
decline.
95:
My allegiance isn't with the Crimson 
Blades, but Alk and Stella, remember?
100:
Haha... Yeah, I almost forgot about 
that.
102:
But if you find yourself needing 
backup, the Crimson Blades have your 
back.
104:
*sigh*
...I've been getting rejected a lot lately, 
haven't I?
108:
I can't allow myself to be at ease just 
yet.
